<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>



table, th, td {
  border: 1px solid black;
  text-align: left;
  border-spacing: 2px;
  padding: 2px;

}

</style>
</head>
<body>
<h1 style="background-color:powderblue;">This is a heading</h1>
<h1 style="color:powderblue;">This is a heading</h1>

<h2>Table With Border</h2>

<p>Use the CSS border property to add a border to the table.</p>

<table style="width:30%">
  <tr>
    <th>Firstname</th>
    <th>Lastname</th> 
    <th>Age</th>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Jill testing for very long name will this wrap?</td>
    <td>Smith</td>
    <td><%= 55/6 %>%</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Eve</td>
    <td>Jackson</td>
    <td>94</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>John</td>
    <td>Doe</td>
    <td>80</td>
  </tr>
</table>

<br>
<br>


<table style="width:50%">

  <tr>
    <th>Goal Name</th>
    <th>Frequency</th> 
    <th>Targeted</th>
    <th>Achieved</th>
    <th>Percentage</th>
  </tr>
  <% @goals.each do |i| %>
  <tr>
    <td><%= i[0] %></td>
    <td><%= i[1] %></td>
    <td><%= i[2] %></td>
    <td><%= i[3] %></td>
    <td><%= i[4] %>%</td>
  </tr>
  <% end %>
</table>

<br>

<table style="width:50%">

  <tr>
    <th width="100">Goal Name</th>
    <th width="50">Frequency</th> 
    <th width="50">Targeted</th>
    <th width="50">Achieved</th>
    <th width="30">Percentage</th>
  </tr>
  <% @goals.each do |i| %>
  <tr>
    <td><%= i[0] %></td>
    <td><%= i[1] %></td>
    <td><%= i[2] %></td>
    <td><%= i[3] %></td>
    <td><%= i[4] %>%</td>
  </tr>
  <% end %>
</table>




</body>
</html>
